cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about character-based neural models for natural language processing tasks, specifically sequence labeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new neural architecture for learning representations of the internal structure of words, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in computer vision, so it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on six different sequence labeling datasets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
